The paper proposes an automated epileptic signal classification method based on modern deep learning methods, specifically a convolutional neural network with residual connections. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for improving clinical practice, indicating that human-computer interaction (cs.HC) may also be a relevant sub-category.
